messageBody:
kick fucking ass. Hmmm....anyone know when cursive
Hebrew was devoloped? Has it existed for ever and a
day, or is it something that was devoloped by the
Israeli state in 1946?

Yours,

Alex


--- Jon Zuck <jz@...> wrote:

> Alex,
>
> That is cursive Hebrew. Some cursive Hebrew letters
> have a very close
> resemblance to Quickscript, for instance Gimel looks
> so much like Kick,
> I think Read might have borrowed its shape
> consciously. (It isn't shown
> in the example.) In the example, the letter that
> looks like QS Mime is
> cursive Hebrew Ayin, and the one that looks like
> Roar is cursive Kaph.
>
> jon
